--

Methodology - Log-Rank Test

$$\text{Log-Rank Test: } \quad \chi^2 = \frac{\left[\sum_i \big(d_{i1} - E(d_{i1})\big)\right]^2}{\sum_i \text{Var}(d_{i1})} = \frac{(O_1 - E_1)^2}{V_1} $$

Methodology - Cox Proportional Hazards Regression Model

$$ \text{Hazard Function: } \quad h_i(t) = h(t \mid \mathbf{x}_i) = h_0(t) \exp(\beta^T \mathbf{x}_i) \qquad \text{Likelihood: } \quad L(\beta, h_0(\cdot)) = \prod_{i=1}^n h(y_i \mid \mathbf{x}_i)^{\delta_i} S(y_i \mid \mathbf{x}_i) $$

$$ \text{Partial Log-Likelihood: } \quad l_{PL}(\beta) = \log L_1(\beta) = \sum_{i=1}^n \delta_i \left\{ \beta^T \mathbf{x}_i - \log \left( \sum_{j \in R(y_i)} e^{\beta^T \mathbf{x}_j} \right) \right\} $$

--

Methodology - Proportional Hazards Assumption & Schoenfeld Residual Test

$$ \text{Proportional Hazards Assumption: } \quad \frac{h(t \mid \mathbf{x}_i)}{h(t \mid \mathbf{x}_j)} = \exp\left(\beta^T (\mathbf{x}_i - \mathbf{x}_j)\right) $$

$$ \text{Schoenfeld Residuals: } \quad r_{i} = \mathbf{x}_i - \frac{\sum_{j \in R(t_i)} \mathbf{x}_j \exp(\beta^T \mathbf{x}_j)} {\sum_{j \in R(t_i)} \exp(\beta^T \mathbf{x}_j)} \qquad \text{Schoenfeld Residual Test Statistic: } \quad \chi^2 = r^T V^{-1} r $$

                   event = Melanoma_df_cleaned$status) ~ sex + ulcer + age + thickness, 
                 method = "breslow", data = Melanoma_df_cleaned)

base_hazard

beta
sex_value1 <- 1
ulcer_value1 <- 1
age_value1 <- 50 
thickness_value1 <- 4.0

  beta["sex"] * sex_value1 +
    beta["ulcer"] * ulcer_value1 +
    beta["age"] * age_value1 +
    beta["thickness"] * thickness_value1))
hazard_ratio1
